kdowns--has amplified the narrative of imminent fatherhood. With $16 million in trading volume, the skin-in-the-game crowd sees his unfiltered influencer persona as a lock for some announcement before December 31. Realistic upsets remain slim but possible: a platform ban amid ongoing outrage, personal change of heart, or legal hurdles derailing his plans.\\\",\\\"context_requires_regen\\\":true,\\\"context_updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-05-01T00:31:22.155Z\\\"}}]\\n\\n[defendant] D-S1 Forbes fragment and limitations\\nRetrieval/extraction notes: curl -L -A 'Mozilla/5.0' fetched the Forbes page. Grep over the HTML/Next.js payload for Clavicular/pregnant/market description terms returned the following relevant page text fragments and metadata.\\n\\nSource metadata:\\n- Title: \\\"Polymarket's $16M Clavicular Bet Sparks Oracle Dispute\\\" / \\\"'Inmates Taking The Asylum'--Polymarket's $16M Clavicular Bet\\\"\\n- Author: Boaz Sobrado\\n- Publisher: Forbes Digital Assets\\n- Published/modified: 2026-04-30T17:55:56-04:00\\n- URL: https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2026/04/30/inmates-taking-the-asylum-polymarkets-16m-clavicular-bet/\\n- Structured metadata description: \\\"Polymarket's $16M Clavicular pregnancy bet is testing UMA's oracle as top traders call the resolution layer 'a disinformation engine taken over by rogue traders.'\\\"\\n- Page metadata says isAccessibleForFree: False.\\n\\nExtracted relevant fragments from article payload:\\n- The disputed market, linked as \\\"Clavicular pregnancy in 2026?\\\", had done $16.46 million in lifetime volume on Polymarket, including roughly $4.5 million in the past 24 hours, and Yes shares traded at 97 cents.\\n- Fragment: \\\"gotten a girl pregnant. The market's own rules state that 'pregnancy announcements that are not credible, for example jokes, will not suffice.' Other traders posting through the dispute, including @holy_mos...\\\"\\n- Fragment: \\\"market description and the platform clarification say No. The price 