ildren. I must get children today\" and \"I will be a dad in the next few months, guys. I am telling you.\"\n- **Express Tribune (D-6/ev_115037a4):** Same contest reporting, quotes: \"I must have children. I must get children today\" and \"I will be a dad in the next few months, guys. I am telling you.\"\n\n**Analysis:**\n- The rule requires a **credible announcement** that Clavicular **and a partner are expecting a baby through pregnancy**.\n- The preserved primary sources (Hindustan Times, Express Tribune, Times of India) all describe Clavicular making **future-oriented statements** about wanting children and proposing a pregnancy contest. These are explicitly characterized as shock content/controversial proposals, not as confirmations of an existing partner pregnancy.\n- The Forbes fragment is the only source pointing to a \"gotten a girl pregnant\" statement, but it is a partial extraction from a metered page with explicit limitations. It does not preserve the full context, original clip, or source chain. Critically, Forbes itself acknowledges the market description and platform clarification said **No**, creating conflict.\n- The Gamma API's event metadata describes the narrative as driven by \"repeated public vows to become a father,\" \"fertility stack reveal,\" and \"controversial pitch for a 'dating show' to select a baby mama\" - again, future aspiration and stunt, not confirmation.\n- The Times of India fact-check explicitly states **no statement from Clavicular confirmed a pregnancy** and **no video confirmed it**. This directly addresses the credited announcement requirement.\n\n**Conclusion:** The preponderance of admitted evidence shows Clavicular made provocative remarks about wanting children and proposing a pregnancy contest, but there is no credible preserved announcement that he and a partner were **already** expecting a baby through pregnancy. The Forbes fragment is insufficient without the missing source chain, and the fuller preserved reporting contradicts the proposition.\n\nTherefore, the proposition is **not demonstrated**."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"hMRxOtkFF","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"mistralai/mistral-medium-3-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782802006796,"responseId":"gen-1782802007-Pif4dQmzCWS3i7TCSQox","responseModel":"mistralai/mistral-medium-3.5-20260430"}}
